{"id": 4113, "title": "Ticket #4113: Add GLOBUS_GATEKEEPER_TIMEOUT -alike to EC2.", "description": "<blockquote>\nThis feature request was prompted by a failure mode of the EC2 tests after implementing <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4004\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4004'); return false;\" title=\"Use POST instead of GET for EC2 Query API for RunInstances\">#4004</a></span>, where an EC2 simulator failure delayed the test suite by an hour.  Although we've since added a shorter time-out for this test, this incident still pointed out the need for a lease on down resources (to prevent us from retrying indefinitely).  Putting the job on hold after this lease expires will cause the test to fail (almost) immediately thereafter.\n\n<p>After implementing this feature, the test suite will need to be modified to set the configuration variable EC2_RESOURCE_TIMEOUT to a very small value.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2013-Dec-11 15:33:07 by tlmiller:</em> <br/>\n\nNote in the documentation that a timeout of -1 is never.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2014-Jan-02 16:15:26 by tlmiller:</em> <br/>\n\nTODO <div class=\"blockquote\">\n<table width=\"95%\"><tbody><tr><td>\u00a0</td><td>\n  After implementing this feature, the test suite will need to be modified to set the configuration variable EC2_RESOURCE_TIMEOUT to a very small value.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Jan-10 10:00</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/62a2481bbb4a030abe1c64fd628586fcc7a25354\">[39132]</a></span>: doc edits for ne